title.narrative: FAMILY STRENGTHENING AND ALTERNATIVE CARE

description.narrative: The social service workforce has increased capacities to provide quality, inclusive family strengthening services and alternative care, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice (Covid), Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: More children, including those affected by humanitarian and emergency situations, will live in safe, non-violent and caring family environments and benefit from increased access to adequate, family-oriented services, quality alternative care, child-sensitive justice and protection from violence

title.narrative: The social service workforce has increased capacities to provide quality, inclusive family strengthening services and alternativecare

description.narrative: In support of government efforts in deinstitutionalization and prevention of child and family separation, UNICEF supports evidence-based policy and programming to accelerate ongoing reform processes towards increasing access to quality family support services and transformation of residential institutions, and capacity building aimed at expanding foster-care capacities.Capacities of the national systems for child protection and migration management have been further strengthened to ensure timely and adequate care for refugee/migrant children and comprehensive fulfilment oftheir ;rights in line with the CRC, with focus on improving sustainability of capacity building and supporting coordination in the area of child protection in emergency. | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/01/2022
